column1: # This file is used to map OSM tags to OM classificator types.
# OSM tags are preprocessed according to data/replaced_tags.txt before this mapping.
# - type name: "highway|bus_stop" ("|" is converted to "-" internally)
# - mapcss selectors for tags: "[highway=bus_stop]", multiple selectors are separated with commas
# - "x" for a deprecated type or an empty cell otherwise
# - optional: a replacement type for a deprecated one
# A "mandatory" mapcss selector like [fee?] or [fee] matches all tag values except [fee=no],
# a "forbidden" selector like [!oneway] matches [oneway=no] only or absence of this tag.
# If first 2 (1 for short types like "building") components of pre-matched types are the same,
# then leave only the longest types (there could be a few of them). Equal arity types are kept.
# - highway-primary-bridge is left while highway-primary is removed
# - building-garages is left while building is removed
# - amenity-parking-underground-fee is left while amenity-parking and amenity-parking-fee are removed
# - both amenity-charging_station-motorcar and amenity-charging_station-bicycle are left
# A shorter format for the above example:
# Works only for simple one tag matching by replacing a "|" with a "=".
# For deprecated types with no replacement put "x" into the last column.
# A deprecated type is not drawn, not searchable, etc. even when using old map files.
# An example of a deprecated type:
# Note there is the old type name and the deprecation date added into a first column.
# Usually we don't re-use deprecated type ids for at least a year
# to avoid breaking experience for users with old maps but a new app version.
# An example of a deprecated type with a replacement:
# First 128 ids are reserved for the most frequently occuring types (they're encoded in 1 byte only).
# Every time you edit this file add/amend unit tests for new/changed matching cases
# in generator/generator_tests/osm_type_test.cpp, build and run the tests:
# A C++ parser implementation used by the generator is in generator/utils.cpp::ParseMapCSS().
# A python parser implementation used to compile *.mapcss style files is in tools/kothic/src/libkomwm.py::komap_mapswithme().
# The app doesn't use this file directly, it loads a data/types.txt
# which is derived from this file during style files compilation.
# Types that don't have any style defined are discarded by the generator.
# To prevent discarding, add them to the exceptions in indexer/feature_visibility.cpp::IsUsefulNondrawableType()
# Paved/formed urban looking footpaths (e.g. paved highway=path are converted into footways, see osm2type.cpp).
# Using service= together with usage=main is a mismapping, but people do it, so exclude explicitly.
# Unpaved paths and trails (e.g. unpaved highway=footway are converted into paths,
# while segregated shared paths into footway + cycleway, see osm2type.cpp).
# Service railway lines, ~1M usages. All service=siding/yard/crossover except =spur (see replaced_tags.txt).
# TODO: railway-rail was deprecated in June 2023 in favor of more detailed railway-rail-main/branch/etc.
# But the type should be kept for some time to retain original styling and translations in older mwms
# and to match some rare combinations like railway=rail usage/service=rare_unsupported_value,
# later such "unsupported" combinations should be replaced with railway-rail-spur or -service.
# TODO: add != matching support to handle "unsupported" values, e.g. [usage!=main].
# Dedicated/segregated cycleways (e.g. segregated paths are converted into cycleways + footways, see osm2type.cpp).
# ~3M usages. TODO: consolidate all other footway=link/etc. values into highway-footway-minor.
# TODO: deprecated, 250k, replace with natural=water + water=reservoir?
# Branch railway lines include ordinary railway=rail w/o any specific usage= or service=, ~500k usages.
# Using service= together with usage=branch is a mismapping, but people do it, so exclude explicitly.
# -spur doesn't include spurs w/ usage= (they're matched to -utility), ~400k usages.
# TODO: do not match this type, so that new railway-rail-main/branch/etc-bridge types are used,
# but retain the old type for compatibility with old mwms for some time.
# In the meantime railway=rail bridge=yes usage=rare_unsupported_value will be matched to railway-rail (not a bridge!).
# Currently its impossible to make unsupported values fallback to railway-rail-bridge
# same way unsupported values fallback to railway-rail, because railway-rail-bridge
# is not a prefix of railway-rail-main|branch|etc-bridge.
# Using a [dont=match] and falling back to just railway-rail seems like the best compromise for now.
# When there is a != and | operators supports, we'll drop this workaround and match like
# TODO: deprecated, <70k as nodes and 95% automated Canada import, we have no point style anyway
# Usually there is something else in place of the old railway, e.g. highway=path,
# but seems like its being used standalone still in which case usefull for e.g. hiking.
# TODO: its a mismapping likely, if there is a bridge structure still, then it should be railway=disused.
# TODO: railway=preserved is deprecated in OSM, recommended mapping is railway:preserved=yes + railway=*
# -utility includes all usage=industrial/military/test/science/freight (see replaced_tags.txt) incl. w/ service=spur, but not w/ other service= values.
# TODO: add [key=value1|value2|etc] (and [key!=value1|value2|etc]) support to avoid referring to replaced_tags.txt.
# TODO: its being replaced by landuse-recreation_ground, merge in there.
# TODO: its a mismapping likely, if there is a tunnel structure still, then it should be railway=disused.
# _path_grade is a surrogate tag which combines sac_scale and trail_visibility, see osm2type.cpp
# _mtb_rating is a mix of mtb:scale, surface smoothness and imba rating, see osm2type
# Useless now, it is detected by the classifier, but has no any rules and isn't set as an exception.
